from @jan_krizaj - - GOING BANANAS FOR BANANAS - 🍌🥥🐒⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
A sustainable drink made from whole banana, focusing on funkyness of the fruit. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
A made a banana oleo which is super simple. I use 50g of sugar per one banana skin and leave it for 48 hours at room temp in a plastic container. After the sugar extracts all the juice from the banana peel you are left with an awesome clear brown syrup that tastes like banana but much more funky and green with rich notes of brown sugar. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Instead of using fresh banana flesh I dehydrated it because I wanted that oxidized banana taste which is much different that fresh, because it becomes more brown and has that caramel touch. Then I infused it into scotch whiskey overnight. So you get two layers of banana funkyness.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I topped the drink with coconut water which adds silky texture with a hint of coconut. But I only added 50ml as I didn’t want to dilute the drink too much. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
